This code reads the number of test cases from the input, and for each test case, it checks if the input string `s` is a substring of the string `"Yes"` repeated 100 times. If it is, it prints "YES", otherwise it prints "NO". 

The `"Yes" * 100` expression repeats the string `"Yes"` 100 times. The `in` operator checks if `s` is a substring of this repeated string. 

The `if __name__ == "__main__":` block is used to ensure that the `solve` function is only called when the script is run directly, not when it is imported as a module.

